         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">About a young woman who comes to the local inn and
                            relates how she had been captured and transported to Marseille. There
                            she was redeemed by Jews from Bordeaux who took her with them. A kohen
                            who had heard about her ransoming wanted to become acquainted with her,
                            but did not want to marry her there because of the grave danger at this
                            place. They traveled together to Geneva via Parma where they could not
                            be found. On the question, if it is permissible for a woman who had been
                            captured to marry and the relevance of testimony of the capture.
                            Benjamin ha-Kohen rules in favor of marriage.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">האלקים אינה לידינו מצוה
                        הבאה</note>
         </notesStmt>
